One person has been killed and twelve others have been injured after a taxi ploughed into two street vendors on a pavement and crashed into a wall.This accident happened on North Coast Road in Durban this morning. When Netcare911 paramedics and other services arrived on scene we found that one of the street vendors had already died due to the extensive injuries he sustained.Netcare911 paramedics declared the man dead on scene.The other street vendor was found to be in a critical condition, he was intubated to help him breathe and airlifted to a trauma 1 facility for further medical care.Reports from the scene indicate that seven people who were passengers in the taxi sustained minor injuries, while four people sustained moderate injuries.All injured were transported by ambulance to various hospitals in the area for further medical care.This accident happened at about 08h00.